headlines.description: — Darius Garland scored 39 points, Evan Mobley added 17 and the Cleveland Cavaliers improved to 8-0 with a 116-114 win on Monday night over the Milwaukee Bucks, who played without injured superstar Giannis Antetokounmpo.
headlines.shortLinkText: Darius Garland scores 39, Cavs improve to 8-0 with 116-114 win over struggling Bucks without Giannis

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry scored 16 of his 24 points in the second half in his return from an ankle injury and the Golden State Warriors won their fourth straight game, 125-112 over the Washington Wizards on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry scores 24 points in his return to lead the Warriors past the Wizards, 125-112

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at Detroit Pistons

headlines.description: — Cade Cunningham had 17 points, 11 rebounds and 11 assists for his third career triple-double and the Detroit Pistons beat the Los Angeles Lakers 115-103 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cunningham has 3rd career triple-double to help the Pistons beat the Lakers, 115-103

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 26 of his 28 points in the first half, and the Boston Celtics routed the Atlanta Hawks 123-93 on Monday night for their third straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jayson Tatum's big first half leads Celtics to 123-93 rout of Hawks

headlines.description: — Dennis Schroder and Cam Johnson each scored 20 points, and the Brooklyn Nets beat the Memphis Grizzlies 106-104 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Schroder and Johnson each score 20 as the Nets beat the Grizzlies 106-104

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis scored off an offensive rebound with 0.7 seconds left, and the Sacramento Kings rallied from 15 points down to beat the Miami Heat 111-110 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sabonis' putback with less than a second left lifts Kings past Heat, 111-110

headlines.description: — Keyonte George had 33 points and nine assists, John Collins added 28 points and 13 rebounds and the Utah Jazz won for the first time this season, beating the Chicago Bulls 135-126 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: George, Collins lead the Jazz to 1st win, 135-126 over the Bulls

events.name: New York Knicks at Houston Rockets

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun had 25 points and 14 rebounds, and the Houston Rockets held on for a 109-97 win over the New York Knicks on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengun has 25 points and 14 rebounds as Houston Rockets hold on for 109-97 win over Knicks

headlines.description: — Naz Reid had 25 points and nine rebounds, and the Minnesota Timberwolves beat the Charlotte Hornets 114-93 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Naz Reid makes five 3-pointers and scores 25 points to lead Timberwolves to 114-93 win over Hornets

events.name: Orlando Magic at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Jalen Williams scored 23 points, Shai Gilgeous-Alexander added 21 points and nine assists and the Oklahoma City Thunder defeated the Orlando Magic 102-86 on Monday night to remain the only unbeaten team in the Western Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Williams, Gilgeous-Alexander help Thunder top Magic and improve to 7-0

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Anfernee Simons scored 24 points, Deandre Ayton had 19 points and 13 rebounds and the Portland Trail Blazers beat the injury-depleted New Orleans Pelicans 118-100 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Anfernee Simons, Deandre Ayton help the Trail Blazers beat the Pelicans, 118-100

headlines.description: — Myles Turner had season highs with 30 points and 11 rebounds while going over 8,000 career points, Tyrese Haliburton had a season-best 25 points and 12 assists and the Indiana Pacers beat the Dallas Mavericks 134-127 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Myles Turner has 30 points and 11 rebounds, the Pacers beat the Mavericks 134-127

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook scored 21 points and played smothering defense on the final play of the game, and the Denver Nuggets beat the Toronto Raptors 121-119 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook scores 21 points, Jokic has a triple-double and the Nuggets beat the Raptors 121-119

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant broke a tie on a driving layup with 24 seconds left and the Phoenix Suns beat Philadelphia 118-116 on Monday night, spoiling Paul George's 76ers debut.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kevin Durant lifts Suns past Philadelphia 118-116, spoiling Paul George's 76ers debut

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Norman Powell scored 23 points, Amir Coffey added 21 and the Los Angeles Clippers rallied from an early 26-point deficit to beat the San Antonio Spurs 113-104 Monday night for their first win at Intuit Dome.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell scores 23, Clippers rally from 26-point deficit to beat Spurs 113-104
